Peter Obi, presidential candidate of the Labour Party (LP), and Datti Baba-Ahmed, his running mate, held a campaign rally in Dutse, the Jigawa capital, on Monday. The LP candidates visited Nuhu Mohammadu Sanusi, the Emir of Dutse, in his palace. Obi and Baba-Ahmed also attended a town hall meeting with youths in the state. Below are pictures.                     